item.title: Google Dashboard. Whadya think?

item.description:

item.title: Google Dashboard. Whadya think?
item.dc:creator: buttlord
item.description:
maybe, but it’s important to remember that they are a company and their first responsibility is producing a profit for their shareholders. They have shown with china that they are not above putting that ahead of the rights of their users.

item.title: Google Dashboard. Whadya think?
item.dc:creator: Level
item.description:
Yes, because they care SO much that you googled porn at 6 am last Tuesday or that you’re doing a science project and only used wikipedia as your sources.

No, they use that information for providing a better product, and so I have no problem giving them some info as long as they put it to good use.

item.title: Google Dashboard. Whadya think?
item.dc:creator: buttlord
item.description:
I dont dislike em really and i use search, gmail and google docs constantly. I just find it a little troubling howmuch info they are able to find about people and how much control they would have on the information available to people if they wanted to effect that for their own ends.
